<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="580" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/224.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul General at
                                    Guayaquil</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Guayaquil</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Montero was sentenced by court martial on January 25 to sixteen
                            years in prison. All other principals were taken to Quito. The mob
                            disapproved the sentence of Montero to mere imprisonment, overpowered
                            the guards, dragged Montero into the street and burned him to death some
                            three blocks from the jail.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dietrich.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>